This paper is primarily focused on the detection of spear phishing emails, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also makes use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the data, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses social features extracted from LinkedIn profiles, which could be considered a form of social network analysis (cs.SI). The paper also makes use of stylometric features extracted from emails, which could be considered a form of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the topic of cybercrime, which could fall under the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
